title: ASX to slip, RBA in focus
summary: Australian shares are set to slip at the open, with sentiment dented by a potential escalation in the trade war between the US and China.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, techs dent Wall Street
summary: Australian shares are poised to end the week on a positive note. Wall St retreats. $A flat.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise on US-China trade hopes
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, buoyed by President Trump's comments that a trade deal with China was closer than many people think.

title: ASX to drop on Trump's China rhetoric, impeachment
summary: Australian shares are poised to tumble 1.2 per cent at the open, as Wall Street fell on weak consumer data and a fresh attack by President Trump on China.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, Euro zone outlook dims
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, as data all but confirmed Germany is in recession and the outlook for Europe has turned bleaker.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to open flat on trade tensions
summary: Australian shares are poised to open little changed after US President Donald Trump said he sees no end in sight to his trade war with China.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, S&P 500 nears record
summary: Microsoft's plan to repurchase up to $US40 billion of its own stock lifted the S&P 500 towards a record high. ASX futures followed. $A sinks on rate cut bets.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Powell reassures
summary: Australian share are set to edge higher. Wall St recouped losses after the Fed signalled policymakers are divided on where rates are heading.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Fed in focus
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher as oil bounced and Wall St rallied into the close. Fed decision awaited.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to slip, Wall St sinks, oil surges
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, as energy stocks helped to check losses on Wall Street. Oil leapt 14% in New York.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to slip, Fed decision awaited

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to rise, Wall St advances
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher as tech stocks extended their rebound and lifted Wall Street. Iron ore surges.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX poised to rise, Apple paces Wall St higher
summary: Enthusiasm with Apple's latest product barrage has bolstered Wall Street and set the stage for an opening advance for Australian shares.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge higher at open

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to open lower

title: ASX set to open lower as hopes checked

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to extend gains on US-China trade hopes

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop on global economic clouds

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to open lower, RBA ahead

title: ASX to start the week with a slip
summary: The fate of pending trade talks between the US and China - and the US Labor Day holiday - is set to keep investors on the defensive as the trading week begins.
